IN a bid to boost Agriculture sector, Coca-Cola Company has introduced soft drinks that will be produced from local fruits producers in the country. Coca-Cola Managing Director, Mr Basil Gadzios made the remark yesterday that the local fruits include fruits like Mango, Apple which are used in production of juice (Minute Maid) from the local fruits producers so as to support the move of the government in industrializing the country. Speaking during the launching of Minute Maid Delight juice, Mr Gadzios said the objective of the launch is to develop a diversified portfolio that drives Coca Cola evolution to become a total beverage company and targets Tanzanian’s fast growing juice category. On her Part, Coca- Cola’s Sales and Marketing Director, Ms Josephine Msalilwa said apart from Tanzania, the company will collect raw materials from other East African countries.